  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nNowdays status-go is generating notifications for both the contact verification _challenger_ and _challengee_. According to [flows in Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=451%3A18681), only the challengee should see declined notifications\r\n\r\nThis is also a bug, because notifications need to filtered out on the client, which doesn't work well with server-side pagination in status-go.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nThe bulk of the work is in status-go, but in status-mobile we should also remove the workaround in https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/9473d3f40cc1b8f182f5a4c63d29e652c71732d4/src/status_im2/contexts/activity_center/notification/contact_verification/view.cljs#L163\r\n\r\n## Scope\r\n\r\nIdentity verification is a feature that may not be enabled in the MVP after all, so before working on this issue, double-check with @cammellos.",
